        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:4:70:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/69/5379",
        "text": [
          " رَجُلٍ قَتَلَ رَجُلاً عَمْداً ثُمَّ فَرَّ فَلَمْ يُقْدَرْ عَلَيْهِ حَتَّى مَاتَ قَالَ \"إِنْ كَانَ لَهُ مَالٌ أُخِذَ مِنْهُ وَ إِلاَّ أُخِذَ مِنَ اَلْأَقْرَبِ فَالْأَقْرَبِ\"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.5379 - Al-Hasan ibn Ali ibn Faddal narrated from Zharif ibn Nasih, from Aban ibn Uthman, from Abu Basir, who narrated from Abu Jafar Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) regarding a man who intentionally killed another man and then fled, and he could not be captured until he died.\nImam (as) said: \"If he had wealth, the blood money is taken from it. If he had no wealth, it is taken from his closest relatives, and then from those next closest to him.\""
          ]
        }
      },
