        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:4:70:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/69/5380",
        "text": [
          " اَلرَّجُلِ يُؤْخَذُ وَ عَلَيْهِ حُدُودٌ إِحْدَاهُنَّ اَلْقَتْلُ قَالَ \"كَانَ عَلِيٌّ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ يُقِيمُ عَلَيْهِ اَلْحُدُودَ قَبْلُ ثُمَّ يَقْتُلُهُ وَ لاَ تُخَالِفْ عَلِيّاً عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ \"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.5380 - Al-Hasan ibn Ali ibn Faddal narrated from Ibn Bukayr, from Ubayd ibn Zurara, who narrated from Abu Abdullah (as) regarding a man who was apprehended with multiple legal punishments (hudud) upon him, one of which was execution.\nImam (as) said: \"Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as) used to carry out the other hudud first and then execute him. Do not oppose Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as).\""
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
